Introduction¶

Diabetes Dataset¶

The data set has ten baseline variables, age, sex, body mass index, average blood pressure, and six blood serum measurements which were obtained for each of 442 diabetes patients. The objective is to find a quantitative measure of disease progression one year after baseline.

Splitting of dataset into training and test sets.¶

Linear Regression Model¶

The green line represents the prediction for the dataset.

Mean squared error for the model: 3887.83
Mean absolue error for the model: 49.13
RMSE for the model is: 62.35
R-Squared for the model is: 0.34

Conclusion¶

From the above plot and the R-squared value it is clear that there is a weak positive correlation between BMI and the diabetes progression for the given dataset.
